The tunnels were dug into cliffs along the River Mersey in Stockport in the 1930s . 
  The space was originally intended to be a car park but was turned into an air raid shelter for residents of Lancashire and Cheshire during the Second World War . 
  The tunnels could hold 6,500 people and had first aid rooms and flush toilets . 
  The shelter was so popular that officials had to issue season tickets . 
 